    {
      "id": "Exercice_03",
      "title": "Exercice 03 (08 pts)",
      "total_exercise_points": "8",
      "introduction_context": "On veut ajouter la structure de donnée matrices ; MAT[i,j] pour être utilisée dans les expressions arithmétiques.",
      "Question": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "question_text": "1. Quelles sont les modifications qui doivent être apportées aux différents fichiers du compilateur (Lex, yacc, type.h).",
          "solution_lex_code": [
            "…",
            "[?:= \\[,\\]] { return(yytext[0]); }",
            "…"
          ],
          "solution_yacc_code": [
            "V : '(' V ')' { $$ = $2; }",
            "  | …",
            "  | TOKEN_VARIABLE '[' C ',' C ']' { $$ = CreerMatrice($1, $3, $5); };",
            "F : '(' C ')' { $$ = $2; }",
            "  | …",
            "  | TOKEN_VARIABLE '[' C ',' C ']' { $$ = CreerMatrice($1, $3, $5); };"
          ],
          "solution_typeh_code": [
            "enum EXPR_TYPE { … , MATRICE };",
            "typedef struct _EXPR_ARBRE {",
            "  enum EXPR_TYPE type;",
            "  union {",
            "    …",
            "    struct {",
            "      char *NOMAT;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *INDL;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *INDC;",
            "    } MATRICE;",
            "    …",
            "  } forme;",
            "} *EXPR_ARBRE;"
          ],
          "level": "Factual"
        },
        {
          "id": "2",
          "question_text": "2. Proposer un modèle de code (d'instructions) MIPS permettant l'accès aux éléments de la matrice.On veut utiliser cette structure (matrice) dans les instructions lecture et affectation",
          "Solution": [
            "# Code pour calculer l'indice de ligne (expression) → $n",
            "# Code pour calculer l'indice de colonne (expression) → $n+1",
            "mul $n, $n, (nombre de colonnes)",
            "add $n, $n, $n+1",
            "li  $n+1, 4",
            "mul $n, $n, $n+1",
            "add $n, $n, $30",
            "lw  $n, d($n)"
          ],
          "level": "Procedural"
        },
        {
          "id": "3",
          "question_text": "3. Proposer la structure d'une déclaration de l'arbre syntaxique des instructions (INST_ARBRE) acceptant la matrice.",
          "solution_typeh_code": [
            "typedef struct _INST_ARBRE {",
            "  enum INST_TYPE type;",
            "  union {",
            "    ...",
            "    struct {",
            "      char *Matrice;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *indiceL;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *indiceC;",
            "    } lecture_Mat;",
            "    struct {",
            "      char *Matrice;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *indiceL;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *indiceC;",
            "      struct _EXPR_ARBRE *expr;",
            "    } Affect_Mat;",
            "    ...",
            "  } forme;",
            "} *INST_ARBRE;"
          ],
          "level": "Conceptual"
        },
        {
          "id": "4",
          "question_text": "4. Ecrire en MNL un programme qui permet de trouver le max d'une matrice.",
          "Solution": [
            "Const N=5, M=5;",
            "Var i, j, Max",
            "Matrice Mat[N,M]",
            "Max := MAT[0,0];",
            "i := 0;",
            "Tantque i<N faire",
            "{ j := 0;",
            "  Tantque j<M faire",
            "  { Lire MAT[i,j];",
            "    j := j+1;",
            "  }",
            "  i := i+1;",
            "}",
            "i := 0;",
            "Tantque i<N faire",
            "{ j := 0;",
            "  Tantque j<M faire",
            "  { Si (MAT[i,j] > max)",
            "      max := MAT[i,j];",
            "    j := j+1;",
            "  }",
            "  i := i+1;",
            "}",
            "Ecrire Max;"
          ],
          "level": "Procedural"
        },
